HEADWORD: Silo
<hw>Si"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A pit or
vat for packing away green fodder for winter use so as to exclude air
and outside moisture. See <er>Ensilage</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silt</ent>⟦br⟧
